ENTRY       EC 1.17.7.2                 Enzyme
NAME        7-hydroxymethyl chlorophyll a reductase;
            HCAR
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on CH or CH2 groups;
            With an iron-sulfur protein as acceptor
SYSNAME     71-hydroxychlorophyll a:ferredoxin oxidoreductase
REACTION    71-hydroxychlorophyll a + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+ = chlorophyll a + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O [RN:R09071]
ALL_REAC    R09071
SUBSTRATE   71-hydroxychlorophyll a;
            reduced ferredoxin [CPD:C00138];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
PRODUCT     chlorophyll a [CPD:C05306];
            oxidized ferredoxin [CPD:C00139];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     Contains FAD and an iron-sulfur center. This enzyme, which is present in plant chloroplasts, carries out the second step in the conversion of chlorophyll b to chlorophyll a (cf. EC 1.1.1.294, chlorophyll(ide) b reductase). It similarly reduces chlorophyllide a.
